The paper focuses on improving the generalization ability of deep learning models, specifically convolutional neural networks, by dropping unfavorable training samples. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses incorporating hand-crafted information into end-to-end learning, which relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed approach involves retraining the model from scratch with a reduced training dataset, which may involve optimization techniques related to neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
